 originated as a local name from any of the various places so called. Examples occur in Derbyshire, Devon, and the West Midlands. The place name has a variety of different origins."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":18,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Shelton Jernegan III was born in 1364, in Somerleyton, Suffolk, England, his father, John Jernegan II, was 24 and his mother, Agatha Geddney Shelton, was 25. He married Margaret Vis de Lou in 1374, in Waveney, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1401, in Conwy, Caernarfonshire, Wales, at the age of 37."},"et":{"1364–1401":"1364–1401","1345–1388":"1345–1388","1380–1450":"1380–1450","1340–1403":"1340–1403","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1403":"1403","1401":"1401","1345":"1345","1388":"1388","1364":"1364","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1450":"1450","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Conwy, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Conwy, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Somerleyton, Suffolk, England":"Somerleyton, Suffolk, England","Waveney, Suffolk, England":"Waveney, Suffolk, England","Somerleyton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Somerleyton, Suffolk, England","Great Yarmouth, Norfolk, England":"Great Yarmouth, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"1364–1401":"1364–1401","1345–1388":"1345–1388","1380–1450":"1380–1450","1340–1403":"1340–1403","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","1403":"1403","1401":"1401","1345":"1345","1388":"1388","1364":"1364","1374":"1374","1340":"1340","1450":"1450","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Conwy, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Conwy, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Somerleyton, Suffol